-- Great Western Rises After Ganzhou Qiandong Rare Earth Agreement
-- B y   S o n j a   E l m q u i s t
-- 2012-01-10T16:15:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-10/great-western-rises-after-ganzhou-qiandong-rare-earth-agreement.html
Great Western Minerals Group (GWMGF) , a
rare-earth alloy producer, rose more than 10 percent after
announcing an accord with Ganzhou Qiandong Rare Earth Group Ltd.
to build a rare-earth plant in  South Africa .  Great Western  jumped  10 percent to C$0.57 at 10:10 a.m. in
Toronto.  Ganzhou Qiandong Rare Earth Group will receive 25 percent
of the venture’s shares and $7.5 million of Great Western shares
during three years, contingent on the plant’s operation,
Saskatoon, Saskatchewan-based Great Western said in a statement
today.  Great Western plans to re-start a previously operating mine
at Steenkamskraal, which will send ore to the venture’s plant
for processing. Great Western produces specialty alloys at
subsidiaries in Birkenhead, U.K. and Troy, Michigan.  The Bloomberg Industries Rare-Earth Mineral Resource  Index (BNREMRS) 
of 21 producers has climbed 19 percent this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
